      "role": "user",
      "content": "smart pointers help with obvious stuff but we have a lot of legacy code with raw pointers that we can't refactor all at once right now because of safety certifications. the leak is really subtle, it's like it only happens under specific interrupt timings. are there specific patterns or \"hidden\" ways memory gets lost that aren't just a missing delete? like, things that happen in the background?",
